{
  "texts": [
    "The criterion for recognizing the stellar sources with consistent stellar atmospheric parameters is that the maximum deviation is less than five times uncertainty, that is,    max({|∆T i eff |}) < 5 × 26 K and max({|∆ log g i |}) < 5 × 0.024 dex and max({|∆[Fe/H] i |}) < 5 × 0.016 dex.",
    "The uncertainties values for effective temperature, surface gravity, and metallicity (26 K, 0.024 dex, and 0.016 dex, respectively) used in Equation (2) are the values corresponding to the peaks of the δT eff, source, δ log g source, and δ[Fe/H] source distributions, as have been given above.",
    "The stellar sources that do not meet this criterion are removed from our sample.",
    "As illustrated in Figure 1, the variations of the Hα profiles caused by stellar activity mainly happen in Hα line center.",
    "In line wings, the spectral profiles of multiple observations are almost identical."
  ]
}